<Author>KayRuth
<Content>Great People, Mediocre Beds We were so pleased with the customer service we received at this hotel. The manager was very gracious and stored our two suitcases in their baggage room a night before our check-in. The service in the restaurant was excellent. Breakfast was included in the package we had booked, and it was quite extensive and tasty, with both hot and cold items. We were happy with the free shuttle service, to and from the airport and train station. The room was modern and clean. This place would be excellent, if the beds had been more comfortable. My bed was quite hard and the mattress seemed worn, as indicated by sagging in the middle. All in all, more good than not, and it's location very close to the airport makes it perfect for grabbing morning flights, but far enough away from any noise. I'd use this place again because of the people and the location. 
