<Author>drumrjohn
<Content>Good Hotel for Road Trip My wife and I spent 2 nights at the Novotel Nord on a recent road-trip from Italy to France. Hotel was clean, restaurant food was very good, bar was open and let us take our after-dinner drinks up to our room without hassle. Large rooms and reception area boasts comfy leather sofas and wi-fi zone. Only complaint was on our 1st night stay: room was very hot, even after we turned thermostat to 0. But the room we occupied on our return journey a week later was just right. Also, beds were more firm than we're used to. All in all, a good hotel. 
