<Author>4-go-travelling
<Content>Service not up to Novotel standard Typical Novotel in terms of rooms and clendliness. However, very badly let down by its staff - most of which appear to work from 6am to midnight every day! Hotel seems to be understaffed so, although it advertises a bar, there are no bar staff so drinks are not available, when we asked to be served a waitress was sent in from the restaurant and was extremely rude to us. The meals were very poor and some were being sent back to be properly cooked - meat was presented almost raw (and I do mean raw not just cooked in the continental style). There are no alternative restaurants in the locality. Location is poor if it is your intention to visit Florence. The free shuttle bus is a bonus but takes about 40 minutes to do the 7km one-away trip. I would not suggest driving yourself as traffic is a nightmare. Has a nice swimming pool. 
